
[1]petrify

   PET'RIFY, v.t. [L. petra; Gr. a stone or rock, and facio, to make.]

   1. To convert to stone or stony substance; as an animal or vegetable
   substance.

   North of Quito,there is a river that petrifies any sort of wood or
   leaves.

   2. To make callous or obdurate; as, to petrify the heart.

   And petrify a genius to a dunce.

   3. To fix; as, to petrify one with astonishment.

    PET'RIFY, v.i. To become stone, or of a stony hardness, as animal or
     vegetable substances by means of calcarious or other depositions in
                               their cavities.
